In 2018, more than 120 girls, trans identified and gender non-binary youth will learn an instrument, form a band and rock out on stage! Building on the successes of past years, we are dedicated to developing and enriching programs that best serve the needs of young rockers in Toronto.In 2018 GRCT is planning:
A March Break Camp in partnership with Dixon Hall Music School 
Two weeks of camp at the Sony Centre for the Performing Arts as well as one week camp out of our home base at the Tranzac. That’s 3 fun-filled summer weeks of music making, learning and dreaming!
A second year of the very electric Rock Camp for Grownups weekend. 
Continuing rehearsal and performance opportunities for participants, year-round.
The development of an early years program geared at children aged 4-7. 
WHAT IS GIRLS ROCK CAMP TORONTO?Girls Rock Camp Toronto is a volunteer based organization that creates the conditions for girls, trans* and gender non-binary youth to learn about themselves and others through music creation. Female-identified and gender non-binary musicians offer music instruction and coach the bands during band practices. We provide a safer space for girls, trans, and gender non-binary youth aged 8-16 to learn instruments, write songs, and rock out on stage. No previous music experience is necessary!Research shows that girls’ self-esteem peaks at age 9, and that seven in ten girls believe they are not good enough or do not measure up in some way, including their looks, performance in school and relationships with friends and family members. More than half of all girls wish they were someone else. At Girls Rock Camp Toronto we help young rockers find their voices through unique programming that combines music education and performance; empowerment and social justice workshops; positive role models, and collaboration and leadership skill building.We are members of the worldwide Girls Rock Camp Alliance and share its values:
We value the power of music as a means to create personal and social change;
We value efforts that actively expand opportunities for girls and women;
We value positive approaches to fighting sexism;
We value integrity, honesty and respect;
We value appropriate sharing of resources, cooperation, and collaboration;
We value using our collective voice to further our mission;
We value diversity.
We value contributing a woman’s voice to the male dominated music industry.
THE GOALIs to raise $12,000 to help us continue to bring positive music-making experiences and practical life skills to countless youth and adults in the GTA. Our mandate is to have a camp that is accessible to people of all economic backgrounds, to do this our tuition is very low and we want to keep it this way. We want to increase the number of subsidized spots and get the word out to youth who would not otherwise hear about camp! Unfortunately, tuition alone does not cover even a third of our expenses. As our demand for camp grows, so do our expenses. So we rely on donations to keep our camp running.Expenses that YOUR donations will cover are:Scholarships: Through this campaign you can choose to sponsor a camper or an entire band, or add to our scholarship fund - helping us offer more subsidized spots so all girls can rock out!Artist Fees: We value the contributions of all of our volunteers! Girls Rock Camp Toronto strives to compensate musicians and artists for their time. Gear: Because we are committed to giving everyone the opportunity to participate in camp, we do not require campers to bring their own instruments and rely on the support of our community to keep our gear in good working condition. We have also established a year-round borrowing program to keep campers rocking all year round! Other music “stuff”: Campers wouldn’t be able to go electric, stay in tune or bring the noise without patch cords, tuners, drumsticks, guitar picks, instrument cases etc.Program Supplies: What would camp be without glitter, glue, paint, silk screen materials, camper notebooks, camper t-shirts, button making supplies, a projector, flip chart paper etc!?Lunch: Everyone gets hungry after practicing guitar kicks and windmills. Logistics: These things may not sound so rock’n’roll, but they are essential to keeping rock camp going: venue rental, insurance costs, accounting and legal services, website hosting and maintenance, graphic design and printing costs for posters, showcase programs and flyers.HOW CAN YOU HELP?To help make Girls Rock Camp Toronto really great, we especially need your money! If you want to be involved but simply do not have the finances-there are other ways you can help. Get the word out about GIRLS ROCK CAMP! By pasting links to this page (facebooking, tweeting, pinteresting, instagramming, tumblring, emailing, etc etc etc)  you are helping spread the word more than we could alone.THE IMPACTBy helping Girls Rock Camp Toronto you are changing the future for young folks! We are inspiring girls, trans and non-binary youth to be who they are and creating the conditions for them to be themselves by rocking out! We know what it's like to grow up without strong women and non-binary role models in music. Here is a chance to support and encourage young rockers to do what they love and have mentors by their side.THANK YOUWe’ve come so far thanks to the help of many GRCT supporters who include:Our incredible volunteer staff of 50+ people who are our band coaches, instrument instructors, support staff, workshop facilitators and all around amazing folks. They give up weeks of their time and measureless amounts of patience, wisdom and mentorship to campers.All the local bands who have played fundraisers in support of GRCT and lunch time bands who inspire young music-makers throughout their week-long songwriting process.The Girls Rock Camp Alliance for their guidance and mentorship.OUR CAMPERS AND THEIR FAMILIES!
